---
import SomeryLayout from "../../layouts/SomeryLayout.astro";
---

<SomeryLayout
  title="Terms of Service — Somery"
  description="Read the Terms of Service for the Somery AI dream journal app."
>
  <section class="section legal-page">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="reveal">
        <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
        <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
        <p class="legal-meta">Last updated: June 30, 2026</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-body reveal">
        <p>
          Please read these Terms of Service ("Terms") carefully before using the
          Somery iOS app ("Service") operated by the Somery team ("we," "us," or
          "our"). By accessing or using the Service you agree to be bound by these
          Terms.
        </p>

        <h2>1. About Somery</h2>
        <p>
          Somery is a personal dream journaling and AI interpretation app available
          on iOS. It lets you record dreams, attach mood and sleep metadata, generate
          AI-powered interpretations and visualisations, and optionally sync your
          journal to the cloud.
        </p>

        <h2>2. Eligibility</h2>
        <p>
          You must be at least 12 years old to use Somery. By creating an account you
          confirm that you meet this age requirement. If you are under 18, you confirm
          that you have your parent or guardian's permission.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Subscriptions and Billing</h2>
        <p>
          Access to AI interpretation features requires an active subscription or
          remaining interpretation credits. Somery offers the following plans:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Weekly</strong> — billed weekly.</li>
          <li><strong>Monthly</strong> — billed monthly, includes a 3-day free trial.</li>
          <li><strong>3-Month</strong> — billed every three months.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          All subscriptions are managed through Apple's App Store and StoreKit.
          Billing, cancellation, and refunds are handled entirely by Apple under
          Apple's own terms and policies. We do not process payments directly and
          have no access to your payment information.
        </p>
        <p>
          To cancel a subscription, manage it through your Apple ID settings. Your
          subscription will remain active until the end of the current billing period.
        </p>

        <h2>4. AI Disclaimer</h2>
        <p>
          Dream interpretations generated by Somery are produced by artificial
          intelligence and are intended for <strong>entertainment and personal
          reflection only</strong>. They are not a substitute for medical,
          psychological, therapeutic, or any other professional advice or treatment.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you are experiencing mental health difficulties, emotional distress, or
          any medical condition, please consult a qualified professional. Do not delay
          or disregard professional advice based on anything generated by the app.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Your Content</h2>
        <p>
          You own the dream journal entries and other content you create in Somery. By
          using the AI interpretation feature, you grant us a limited, non-exclusive
          licence to transmit that content to our AI provider (OpenAI) solely for the
          purpose of generating your requested interpretation. We do not use your dream
          content to train AI models.
        </p>
        <p>
          You are responsible for the content you enter. Do not submit content that is
          unlawful, harmful, or that violates the rights of others.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Acceptable Use</h2>
        <p>You agree to use Somery for lawful, personal purposes only. You must not:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Use the app to harass, abuse, or harm any person.</li>
          <li>Attempt to reverse-engineer, decompile, or tamper with the app.</li>
          <li>Use automated tools to scrape or extract data from the Service.</li>
          <li>Use the Service for any illegal purpose or in violation of any applicable law.</li>
          <li>Attempt to gain unauthorised access to any part of the Service or its infrastructure.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>7. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
          The Somery app, including its design, code, branding, and original content,
          is owned by us and protected by intellectual property laws. Nothing in these
          Terms transfers any ownership rights to you.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
        <p>
          The Service is provided <strong>"as is"</strong> and <strong>"as
          available"</strong> without warranties of any kind, either express or
          implied, including but not limited to implied warranties of merchantability,
          fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement. We do not warrant
          that the Service will be uninterrupted, error-free, or free of harmful
          components.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the fullest extent permitted by law, we shall not be liable for any
          indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, or any
          loss of profits or revenues, whether incurred directly or indirectly, arising
          out of your use of or inability to use the Service. Our total liability for
          any claim arising from these Terms or your use of the Service shall not
          exceed the amount you paid us in the twelve months preceding the claim.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Termination</h2>
        <p>
          We reserve the right to suspend or terminate your account if you violate
          these Terms. You may terminate your account at any time through
          <strong>Settings → Data Management</strong> in the app. Upon termination,
          your right to use the Service ceases immediately.
        </p>

        <h2>11. Changes to These Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We may update these Terms from time to time. We will notify you of material
          changes by updating the "Last updated" date at the top of this page.
          Continued use of the app after changes are posted constitutes acceptance of
          the revised Terms.
        </p>

        <h2>12. Governing Law</h2>
        <p>
          This agreement is governed by the laws of Ukraine, without regard to
          its conflict of law provisions.
        </p>

        <h2>13. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have questions about these Terms, please contact us at
          <a href="mailto:support@somery.app">support@somery.app</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</SomeryLayout>
